<PolicyPage ID="x10951" Name="Occupancy Guidelines" Layout="general_Policy.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Policy Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">What are the occupancy guidelines at University Village?</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Policy Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">There are maximum occupancy guidelines in place at University Village. Click to learn more.</Abstract><Date type="date" label="Revision Date" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true" display="localdateshort" UTC="true">20110101T07:00:00</Date><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Policy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>&nbsp;</p>
<hr />
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Note: The University Village apartment contract-holder must be a matriculating student (in other words, assigned to a track and in good standing with the university). Loss of student status (including graduation) disqualifies tenants from living in University Village.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>This is probably also a good place to mention that no pets (including therapy animals with a perscription) are allowed at University Village.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If you have any questions, <a href="x9184.xml">c</a><a href="x9184.xml">ontact the University Village managers</a> for more information.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
